item.title: Jdk
item.description:
@000286 wrote:

Go to Control Panel then System, then Advanced and at the bottom it will have an option for “Environmental Variables” oopen that and in the top box click new and name one “CLASSPATH” and for the text put in “CLASSPATH=C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_02\bin;%CLASSPATH%;” And now OK Then click new again and type in “PATH” and for the text “C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_02\bin;” Then click OK, Then OK again then OK again. Now where you see in the text “jdk1.6.0_02” See the 2? If you have version 6 chnage it to 6, if 7, change to 7, recurring. Same thing with both of them. Hope this helps you.
